  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>butter </strong>over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once melted, add your <strong>curry powder </strong>and stir for 30 secs, then transfer the <strong>curried butter</strong> to a bowl to cool</p><p>Wipe the pan clean and reserve it for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your<strong> smoked basa fillet[s]</strong> with kitchen paper and add to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season lightly with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the smoked basa is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Reboil half a kettle (you'll only need a little!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then chop your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> roughly</p><p>Wash, your <strong>spring greens</strong> then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Stir your <strong>mayo </strong>and<strong> white wine vinegar </strong>into the <strong>cooled</strong> <strong>curried butter </strong>along with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>curried mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452-Step-4-shallot-1633423854029-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452-Step-4-shallot-1633423854029-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452-Step-4-shallot-1633423854029-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452-Step-4-shallot-1633423854029-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452-Step-4-shallot-1633423854029-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> panko breadcrumbs </strong>to a plate</p><p>Run the<strong> potatoes</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until cool enough to handle, then return to the pot and crush gently</p><p>Using a fork, flake the <strong>cooked smoked basa</strong> into the crushed potatoes, add the<strong> chopped spring onion </strong>and plenty of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> then mix gently</p><p>Divide the mix into 2 fishcakes per person, then press into the <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>firmly to evenly coat</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/452.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
